      "widgets_values": [
        "The main subject is a person's head and upper shoulders, positioned centrally in the frame. The person appears to have light skin with visible freckling across the forehead, nose, and cheeks. The individual has light-colored hair, though the hair itself is largely obscured by flowers and particles. The facial features include defined eyebrows, blue eyes that are looking directly forward, a straight nose, and full lips that are painted a muted reddish-pink color. The person's expression is neutral. The subject is adorned with several artificial flowers placed across the forehead and around the face. To the left, there is a large, bright red flower with multiple visible petals and a darker center. To the right, there is a prominent white flower with several distinct petals and a visible yellow-orange center. A smaller white flower is positioned slightly above and to the right of the red flower. The entire visible skin surface, particularly the face and neck, is covered in a dense scattering of small, white, particulate matter, resembling glitter or fine dust.\n\nThere are no discernible secondary elements other than the flowers and the particulate matter covering the subject.\n\nThe setting appears to be a studio environment, as the background is uniformly black, offering no discernible architectural or environmental details.\n\nThe shot is a close-up portrait, framing the face and upper chest of the subject. The depth of field keeps the face and the flowers relatively sharp, while the background falls into deep shadow.\n\nThe lighting is dramatic, coming from the front and slightly above, illuminating the face and causing strong highlights on the skin and the petals of the flowers. The light source emphasizes the texture of the freckles and the reflective quality of the white particles. Shadows are deep, particularly around the neck and beneath the chin area.\n\nThe dominant color palette is composed of deep blacks from the background, contrasted sharply with the bright whites of the flowers and particles, the vivid red of the flower on the left, and the natural skin tones of the subject. The textures visible include the soft, matte appearance of the petals, the granular, slightly rough texture of the freckled skin, and the highly reflective, scattered texture of the white particles covering the skin."
      ]
